  43,2,By the clear Book
  43,3,"Certainly, We have made it a Quran in Arabic so perhaps you will understand"
  43,4,"And indeed, it is‚ÄĒin the Master Record¬†with Us‚ÄĒhighly esteemed, rich in wisdom"
  43,5,Should We then turn the ňĻQuranicňļ Reminder away from you ňĻsimplyňļ because you have been a transgressing people
  43,6,ňĻImagineňļ how many prophets We sent to those ňĻdestroyedňļ before
  43,7,But no prophet ever came to them without being mocked
  43,8,So We destroyed those who were far mightier than these ňĻMeccansňļ. The examples of ňĻtheirňļ predecessors have ňĻalreadyňļ been related
  43,9,"If you ask them ňĻO Prophetňļ who created the heavens and the earth, they will certainly say, ‚ÄúThe Almighty, All-Knowing did.‚ÄĚ"
  43,10,"ňĻHe is the Oneňļ Who has laid out the earth for you, and set in it pathways for you so that you may find your way"
  43,11,"And ňĻHe is the Oneňļ Who sends down rain from the sky in perfect measure, with which We give life to a lifeless land. And so will you be brought forth ňĻfrom the graveňļ"
  43,12,"And ňĻHe is the Oneňļ Who created all ňĻthings inňļ pairs,¬†and made for you ships and animals to ride"
  43,13,"so that you may sit firmly on their backs, and remember your Lord‚Äôs blessings once you are settled on them, saying, ‚ÄúGlory be to the One Who has subjected these for us, for we could have never done so ňĻon our ownňļ"
  43,14,And surely to our Lord we will ňĻallňļ return.‚ÄĚ
  43,15,"Still the pagans have made some of His creation out to be a part of Him.¬†Indeed, humankind is clearly ungrateful"
  43,16,"Has He taken ňĻangels as Hisňļ daughters from what He created, and favoured you ňĻO pagansňļ with sons"
  43,17,"Whenever one of them is given the good news of what they attribute to the Most Compassionate,¬†his face grows gloomy, as he suppresses his rage"
  43,18,ňĻDo they attribute to Himňļ those who are brought up in fineries and are not commanding in disputes
  43,19,"Still they have labelled the angels, who are servants of the Most Compassionate, as female. Did they witness their creation? Their statement will be recorded, and they will be questioned"
  43,20,"And they argue, ‚ÄúHad the Most Compassionate willed, we would have never worshipped them.‚ÄĚ They have no knowledge ňĻin supportňļ of this ňĻclaimňļ. They do nothing but lie"
  43,21,"Or have We given them a Book ňĻfor proofňļ, before this ňĻQuranňļ, to which they are holding firm"
  43,22,"In fact, they say, ‚ÄúWe found our forefathers following a ňĻparticularňļ way, and we are following in their footsteps.‚ÄĚ"
  43,23,"Similarly, whenever We sent a warner to a society before you ňĻO Prophetňļ, its ňĻspoiledňļ elite would say, ‚ÄúWe found our forefathers following a ňĻparticularňļ way, and we are walking in their footsteps.‚ÄĚ"
  43,24,"Each ňĻwarnerňļ asked, ‚ÄúEven if what I brought you is better guidance than what you found your forefathers practicing?‚ÄĚ They replied, ‚ÄúWe totally reject whatever you have been sent with.‚ÄĚ"
  43,25,So We inflicted punishment upon them. See then what was the fate of the deniers
  43,26,"ňĻRemember, O Prophetňļ when Abraham declared to his father and his people, ‚ÄúI am totally free of whatever ňĻgodsňļ you worship"
  43,27,"except the One Who originated me, and He will surely guide me.‚ÄĚ"
  43,28,"And he left this enduring declaration among his descendants, so they may ňĻalwaysňļ turn back ňĻto Allahňļ"
  43,29,"In fact, I had allowed enjoyment for these ňĻMeccansňļ and their forefathers, until the truth came to them along with a messenger making things clear"
  43,30,"ňĻButňļ when the truth came to them, they said, ‚ÄúThis is magic, and we totally reject it.‚ÄĚ"
  43,31,"And they exclaimed, ‚ÄúIf only this Quran was revealed to a great man from ňĻone ofňļ the two cities!‚ÄĚ"
  43,32,Is it they who distribute your Lord‚Äôs mercy? We ňĻaloneňļ have distributed their ňĻveryňļ livelihood among them in this worldly life and raised some of them in rank above others so that some may employ others in service. ňĻButňļ your Lord‚Äôs mercy is far better than whatever ňĻwealthňļ they amass
  43,33,"Were it not that people might ňĻbe tempted toňļ become one community ňĻof disbelieversňļ, We would have supplied the homes of ňĻonlyňļ those who disbelieve in the Most Compassionate with silver roofs and ňĻsilverňļ stairways to ascend"
  43,34,as well as ňĻsilverňļ gates and thrones to recline on
  43,35,and ornaments ňĻof goldňļ. Yet all this is no more than a ňĻfleetingňļ enjoyment in this worldly life. ňĻButňļ the Hereafter with your Lord is ňĻonlyňļ for those mindful ňĻof Himňļ
  43,36,"And whoever turns a blind eye to the Reminder of the Most Compassionate, We place at the disposal of each a devilish one as their close associate"
  43,37,who will certainly hinder them from the ňĻRightňļ Way while they think they are ňĻrightlyňļ guided
  43,38,"But when such a person comes to Us, one will say ňĻto their associateňļ, ‚ÄúI wish you were as distant from me as the east is from the west! What an evil associate ňĻyou wereňļ!‚ÄĚ"
  43,39,"ňĻIt will be said to both,ňļ ‚ÄúSince you all did wrong, sharing in the punishment will be of no benefit to you this Day.‚ÄĚ"
  43,40,"Can you make the deaf hear, or guide the blind or those clearly astray"
  43,41,"Even if We take you away ňĻfrom this worldňļ, We will surely inflict punishment upon them"
  43,42,"Or if We show you what We threaten them with, We certainly have full power over them"
  43,43,So hold firmly to what has been revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ. You are truly on the Straight Path
  43,44,Surely this ňĻQuranňļ is a glory for you and your people. And you will ňĻallňļ be questioned ňĻabout itňļ
  43,45,Ask ňĻthe followers ofňļ the messengers that We already sent before you if We ňĻeverňļ appointed ňĻotherňļ gods to be worshipped besides the Most Compassionate
  43,46,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs, and he said: ‚ÄúI am a messenger of the Lord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  43,47,"But as soon as he came to them with Our signs, they laughed at them"
  43,48,"although every sign We showed them was greater than the one before.¬†Ultimately, We seized them with torments so that they might return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  43,49,"ňĻThenňļ they pleaded, ‚ÄúO ňĻmightyňļ magician! Pray to your Lord on our behalf, by virtue of the covenant He made with you.¬†We will certainly accept guidance.‚ÄĚ"
  43,50,"But as soon as We removed the torments from them, they broke their promise"
  43,51,"And Pharaoh called out to his people, boasting, ‚ÄúO my people! Am I not sovereign over Egypt as well as ňĻallňļ these streams¬†flowing at my feet? Can you not see"
  43,52,Am I not better than this nobody who can hardly express himself
  43,53,Why then have no golden bracelets ňĻof kingshipňļ been granted to him or angels come with him as escorts!‚ÄĚ
  43,54,"And so he fooled his people, and they obeyed him. They were truly a rebellious people"
  43,55,"So when they enraged Us, We inflicted punishment upon them, drowning them all"
  43,56,And We made them an example and a lesson for those after them
  43,57,"When the son of Mary was cited as an example ňĻin argumentňļ, your people ňĻO Prophetňļ broke into ňĻjoyfulňļ applause"
  43,58,"They exclaimed, ‚ÄúWhich is better: our gods or Jesus?‚ÄĚ They cite him only to argue. In fact, they are a people prone to dispute"
  43,59,"He was only a servant We showed favour to, and made as an example for the Children of Israel"
  43,60,"Had We willed, We could have easily replaced you ňĻallňļ with angels,¬†succeeding one another on earth"
  43,61,"And his ňĻsecondňļ coming is truly a sign for the Hour. So have no doubt about it, and follow me. This is the Straight Path"
  43,62,"And do not let Satan hinder you, ňĻforňļ he is certainly your sworn enemy"
  43,63,"When Jesus came with clear proofs, he declared, ‚ÄúI have come to you with wisdom, and to clarify to you some of what you differ about. So fear Allah, and obey me"
  43,64,"Surely Allah ňĻaloneňļ is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him ňĻaloneňļ. This is the Straight Path.‚ÄĚ"
  43,65,"Yet their ňĻvariousňļ groups have differed among themselves ňĻabout himňļ, so woe to the wrongdoers when they face the torment of a painful Day"
  43,66,Are they waiting for the Hour to take them by surprise when they least expect ňĻitňļ
  43,67,"Close friends will be enemies to one another on that Day, except the righteous"
  43,68,"ňĻwho will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúO My servants! There is no fear for you Today, nor will you grieve‚ÄĒ"
  43,69,ňĻthoseňļ who believed in Our signs and ňĻfullyňļ submitted ňĻto Usňļ
  43,70,"Enter Paradise, you and your spouses, rejoicing.‚ÄĚ"
  43,71,Golden trays and cups will be passed around to them. There will be whatever the souls desire and the eyes delight in. And you will be there forever
  43,72,That is the Paradise which you will be awarded for what you used to do
  43,73,There you will have abundant fruit¬†to eat from
  43,74,"Indeed, the wicked will be in the torment of Hell forever"
  43,75,"It will never be lightened for them, and there they will be overwhelmed with despair"
  43,76,"We did not wrong them, but it was they who were the wrongdoers"
  43,77,"They will cry, ‚ÄúO M√Ęlik!¬†Let your Lord finish us off.‚ÄĚ He will answer, ‚ÄúYou are definitely here to stay.‚ÄĚ"
  43,78,"We certainly brought the truth to you, but most of you were resentful of the truth"
  43,79,Or have they mastered some ňĻevilňļ plan? Then We ňĻtooňļ are surely planning
  43,80,"Or do they think that We do not hear their ňĻevilňļ thoughts and secret talks? Yes ňĻWe doňļ! And Our messenger-angels are in their presence, recording ňĻit allňļ"
  43,81,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIf the Most Compassionate ňĻreallyňļ had offspring, I would be the first worshipper.‚ÄĚ"
  43,82,"Glorified is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne, far above what they claim"
  43,83,"So let them indulge ňĻin falsehoodňļ and amuse ňĻthemselvesňļ until they face their Day, which they have been warned of"
  43,84,"It is He Who is ňĻthe onlyňļ God in the heavens and ňĻthe onlyňļ God on the earth. For He is the All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  43,85,And Blessed is the One to Whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything in between! With Him ňĻaloneňļ is the knowledge of the Hour. And to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned
  43,86,"ňĻButňļ those ňĻobjects of worshipňļ they invoke besides Him have no power to intercede, except those who testify to the truth knowingly"
  43,87,"If you ask them ňĻO Prophetňļ who created them, they will certainly say, ‚ÄúAllah!‚ÄĚ How can they then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
